parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The death wobble/steering wobble can cause the vehicle to become unstable, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of life.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or wobbles violently
especially when driving at high speeds
crossing dips or bumps in the road
or when towing a trailer. The steering wheel may seize or become difficult to control
and the vehicle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The violent shaking of the front end, also known as the "Ford Death Wobble," can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: while driving at high speeds (40-60 mph)
especially on bumpy terrain or when cornering; the steering wheel shakes severely; the vehicle may pull to one side or vibrate excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to run rough, lack power, and blow black smoke, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The rusty fuel tank lining can cause the fuel system to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: pieces of rust in the bottom of the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high-pressure fuel system can cause the vehicle to run rough, lack power, and blow black smoke, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: frequent repairs to the high-pressure fuel system.
